should have been holding had somehow pierced through my
core.

which should have been exhausted, remain?

"Hey... don't say things like that."\n<Yukine>

"I'm sorry. You're right, there's no way such a cute old

"Geez... Saku, you've become quite the chatterbox, haven't
you?"\n<Yukine>

I've heard a lot from Saku since then. Saku Kagetsuki is a
divine being that descended from the moon and resided in an
ancient stone.

Unable to return to the moon, she slept alone in the
mountains for a long time. She met a young girl and gained
many emotions. And unable to forget the warmth of people,
she twisted her divinity in solitude and fell.

All of that, Saku, who inherited the memories and power,
taught me bit by bit.

"But we were really lucky, weren't we? Even though our
divine statuses were completely different."\n<Yukine>

"Surely, Saku Kagetsuki-sama must have longed for warmth
too."\n<Saku>

"She must have been so lonely that she even forgot her own
name... Saku Kagetsuki-sama..."\n<Yukine>

"But now we're together, so let's leave the gloomy stories
behind."\n<Saku>
"It's about time for a walk, isn't it? Yukine Onee-san."\n<Saku>

"That's right, Saku. The weather is nice today as well, so
let's go for a walk."\n<Saku>
